            reviewDate: 'July 31, 2023',
            semester: 'summer 2023',
            review: "This course is fairly interesting in the beginning but then the lectures and content become a drag. Some of the concepts are a bit outdated but the overall lessons are still important. Out of everything I learned, I think understanding the different diagrams (class model diagrams, sequence diagrams, etc) are the most useful thing to learn and understand. As for projects, I took this class in Summer 2023 and timing is a big issue. The first 2 projects are fairly easy and they give you 3 weeks (2 for the 1st and 1 for the second) to finish them. This honestly is too much time, in reality, they should make the 1st project only 1 week and add the extra week to project 5. Taking this class in the summer does put an extra time constraint as well. All the projects in this class build on each other for the final group project and you should definitely try to find a good team. The last 2 weeks are definitely the most amount of work since that is when the group project opens and you don't have a lot of time to finish it. I personally spent 5 hours a week doing the projects, and quizzes, and watching the lectures for the majority of the time. The last 2 weeks are when I spent about 30 hours/week working on the group project.",
