            review: "Better take my words and stay away from this course. This is one of the most mismanaged courses in in the OMS program. The projects are made unnecessarily complex by giving vague data. The projects wont open early. The TAs will take days to respond, finally you will be left with just one weekend to do all the project coding. Many of the TAs work remotely and I had a TA who had completely opposite timezone as mine. You need to stay awake late nights to communicate via teams and their responses take hours. Since I took this for summer, some of the lectures were mentioned optional. But they would expect to attend the practice quizzes for the optional lectures too!! The group project is a total disaster. You will be given just one week to complete it along with colleagues who don't know anything about coding.",
