        'spring 2015':
            'The course offers a substantial workload and varies significantly in teaching style depending on the professor, making it a challenge, especially when taken alongside other courses. However, students appreciate the depth and importance of the subjects covered, which enhance their domain knowledge. Many find the course intriguing, especially with its unique perspective on UML and OOAD, vital for understanding real-life applications. Familiarity with ILP and Java is necessary, as there are no definitive answers to projects, reflecting the ambiguity of real-world requirements. Overall, taking the course with an open mind yields a valuable learning experience, despite its challenges.',
